==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{qualifier|abbreviation}}: {{l|en|sg.}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|singuler|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|singularis||alone of its kind|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|singulus||single|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-singular.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Being only one of a larger population.
#: ''A '''singular''' experiment cannot be regarded as scientific proof of the existence of a phenomenon.''
# Being the only one of the kind; unique.
#: ''She has a '''singular''' personality.''
#* Addison
#*: These busts of the emperors and empresses are all very scarce, and some of them almost '''singular''' in their kind.
#* Chaucer
#*: And God forbid that all a company / Should rue a '''singular''' man's folly.
#: {{rfquotek|Francis Bacon}}
# Distinguished by superiority; eminent; extraordinary; exceptional.
#: ''a man of '''singular''' gravity or attainments''
# Out of the ordinary; curious.
#: ''It was very '''singular'''; I don't know why he did it.''
#* Denham
#*: So '''singular''' a sadness / Must have a cause as strange as the effect.
#* Milton
#*: His zeal / None seconded, as out of season judged, / Or '''singular''' and rash.
# {{context|grammar|lang=en}} Referring to only one thing or person.
# {{context|linear algebra|of matrix|lang=en}} Having no [[inverse]].
# {{context|linear algebra|of transformation|lang=en}} Having the property that the matrix of coefficients of the new variables has a determinant equal to zero.
# {{context|set theory|of a cardinal number|lang=en}} Not equal to its own {{l/en|cofinality}}.
# {{cx|legal|lang=en}} Each; individual.
#: ''to convey several parcels of land, all and '''singular'''''
# {{cx|obsolete|lang=en}} Engaged in by only one on a side; single.
#* Holinshed
#*: to try the matter thus together in a '''singular''' combat

